            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20return%20of%20the%20king%20was%20a%20sudden%2C%20unanticipated%20event%20that%20radically%20changed%20all%20perspectives.%20Those%20who%20had%20mocked%20David%20as%20he%20left%20Jerusalem%20now%20repented%2C%20falling%20prostrate%20and%20begging%20for%20mercy.%20Those%20who%20had%20blessed%20David%20in%20his%20exile%20were%20richly%20rewarded%20(2%20Samuel%2019%3A23)%20and%20invited%20to%20sit%20at%20his%20table%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives.%20With%20his%20return%2C%20David%20held%20accountable%20those%20whose%20actions%20were%20questionable%2C%20and%20the%20truth%20was%20revealed%20(v.%2025).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhat%20a%20picture%20this%20story%20is%20of%20the%20return%20of%20the%20King%20of%20Kings!%20When%20Jesus%20returns%2C%20time%20will%20stop.%20One%20by%20one%2C%20we%20will%20each%20stand%20before%20the%20judgment%20seat%20of%20Christ%20and%20give%20a%20detailed%20account%20of%20how%20we%20have%20used%20our%20time%2C%20money%2C%20and%20gifts.%20We%20will%20answer%20for%20every%20wrong%20thought%20and%20attitude%20of%20the%20mind%20we%20have%20harbored.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20foolish%20it%20is%20to%20waste%20our%20lives%20or%20brazenly%20defy%20the%20Lordship%20of%20Christ%20as%20though%20He%20will%20never%20return!%20Why%20not%20ponder%20every%20day%20what%20it%20will%20be%20like%20the%20moment%20after%20the%20King%20returns%20and%20it%20is%20too%20late%20to%20change%20anything%3F%20One%20day%20our%20King%20will%20return.%20That%20is%20a%20sure%20fact.%20May%20you%20hear%20Him%20say%2C%20%22Well%20done%2C%20my%20good%20and%20faithful%20servant%22%20(Matthew%2025%3A21).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
