            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Samuel.19:11-20:13",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Samuel%2019%3A11-20%3A13%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20King%20David%20sent%20Zadok%20and%20Abiathar%2C%20the%20priests%2C%20to%20say%20to%20the%20elders%20of%20Judah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20are%20you%20the%20last%20ones%20to%20welcome%20back%20the%20king%20into%20his%20palace%3F%20For%20I%20have%20heard%20that%20all%20Israel%20is%20ready.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_12%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EYou%20are%20my%20relatives%2C%20my%20own%20tribe%2C%20my%20own%20flesh%20and%20blood!%20So%20why%20are%20you%20the%20last%20ones%20to%20welcome%20back%20the%20king%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_13%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20David%20told%20them%20to%20tell%20Amasa%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BSince%20you%20are%20my%20own%20flesh%20and%20blood%2C%20like%20Joab%2C%20may%20God%20strike%20me%20and%20even%20kill%20me%20if%20I%20do%20not%20appoint%20you%20as%20commander%20of%20my%20army%20in%20his%20place.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_14%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Amasa%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EDavid%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ehe.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20convinced%20all%20the%20men%20of%20Judah%2C%20and%20they%20responded%20unanimously.%20They%20sent%20word%20to%20the%20king%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BReturn%20to%20us%2C%20and%20bring%20back%20all%20who%20are%20with%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_15%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Return%20to%20Jerusalem%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20king%20started%20back%20to%20Jerusalem.%20And%20when%20he%20arrived%20at%20the%20Jordan%20River%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Judah%20came%20to%20Gilgal%20to%20meet%20him%20and%20escort%20him%20across%20the%20river.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_16%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EShimei%20son%20of%20Gera%2C%20the%20man%20from%20Bahurim%20in%20Benjamin%2C%20hurried%20across%20with%20the%20men%20of%20Judah%20to%20welcome%20King%20David.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_17%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EA%20thousand%20other%20men%20from%20the%20tribe%20of%20Benjamin%20were%20with%20him%2C%20including%20Ziba%2C%20the%20chief%20servant%20of%20the%20house%20of%20Saul%2C%20and%20Ziba%26%23x2019%3Bs%20fifteen%20sons%20and%20twenty%20servants.%20They%20rushed%20down%20to%20the%20Jordan%20to%20meet%20the%20king.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_18%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20crossed%20the%20shallows%20of%20the%20Jordan%20to%20bring%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20household%20across%20the%20river%2C%20helping%20him%20in%20every%20way%20they%20could.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Mercy%20to%20Shimei%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3EAs%20the%20king%20was%20about%20to%20cross%20the%20river%2C%20Shimei%20fell%20down%20before%20him.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_19%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BMy%20lord%20the%20king%2C%20please%20forgive%20me%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20pleaded.%20%26%23x201C%3BForget%20the%20terrible%20thing%20your%20servant%20did%20when%20you%20left%20Jerusalem.%20May%20the%20king%20put%20it%20out%20of%20his%20mind.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_20%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20know%20how%20much%20I%20sinned.%20That%20is%20why%20I%20have%20come%20here%20today%2C%20the%20very%20first%20person%20in%20all%20Israel%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ein%20the%20house%20of%20Joseph.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20to%20greet%20my%20lord%20the%20king.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_21%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Abishai%20son%20of%20Zeruiah%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BShimei%20should%20die%2C%20for%20he%20cursed%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anointed%20king!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_22%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWho%20asked%20your%20opinion%2C%20you%20sons%20of%20Zeruiah!%26%23x201D%3B%20David%20exclaimed.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20have%20you%20become%20my%20adversary%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A22%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Emy%20prosecutor.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20today%3F%20This%20is%20not%20a%20day%20for%20execution%2C%20for%20today%20I%20am%20once%20again%20the%20king%20of%20Israel!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_23%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%2C%20turning%20to%20Shimei%2C%20David%20vowed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYour%20life%20will%20be%20spared.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_24%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Kindness%20to%20Mephibosheth%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20Mephibosheth%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A24%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cem%3EMephibosheth%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20another%20name%20for%20Merib-baal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20grandson%2C%20came%20down%20from%20Jerusalem%20to%20meet%20the%20king.%20He%20had%20not%20cared%20for%20his%20feet%2C%20trimmed%20his%20beard%2C%20or%20washed%20his%20clothes%20since%20the%20day%20the%20king%20left%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_25%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20didn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20you%20come%20with%20me%2C%20Mephibosheth%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20king%20asked%20him.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_26%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EMephibosheth%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20lord%20the%20king%2C%20my%20servant%20Ziba%20deceived%20me.%20I%20told%20him%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BSaddle%20my%20donkey%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A26%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%2C%20Syriac%2C%20and%20Latin%20versions%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EI%20will%20saddle%20a%20donkey%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20so%20I%20can%20go%20with%20the%20king.%26%23x2019%3B%20For%20as%20you%20know%20I%20am%20crippled.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_27%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3EZiba%20has%20slandered%20me%20by%20saying%20that%20I%20refused%20to%20come.%20But%20I%20know%20that%20my%20lord%20the%20king%20is%20like%20an%20angel%20of%20God%2C%20so%20do%20what%20you%20think%20is%20best.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_28%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EAll%20my%20relatives%20and%20I%20could%20expect%20only%20death%20from%20you%2C%20my%20lord%2C%20but%20instead%20you%20have%20honored%20me%20by%20allowing%20me%20to%20eat%20at%20your%20own%20table!%20What%20more%20can%20I%20ask%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_29%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BYou%26%23x2019%3Bve%20said%20enough%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20David%20replied.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%26%23x2019%3Bve%20decided%20that%20you%20and%20Ziba%20will%20divide%20your%20land%20equally%20between%20you.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_30%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BGive%20him%20all%20of%20it%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Mephibosheth%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20content%20just%20to%20have%20you%20safely%20back%20again%2C%20my%20lord%20the%20king!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_31%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Kindness%20to%20Barzillai%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EBarzillai%20of%20Gilead%20had%20come%20down%20from%20Rogelim%20to%20escort%20the%20king%20across%20the%20Jordan.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_32%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20was%20very%20old%26%23x2014%3Beighty%20years%20of%20age%26%23x2014%3Band%20very%20wealthy.%20He%20was%20the%20one%20who%20had%20provided%20food%20for%20the%20king%20during%20his%20stay%20in%20Mahanaim.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_33%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BCome%20across%20with%20me%20and%20live%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20the%20king%20said%20to%20Barzillai.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20will%20take%20care%20of%20you%20there.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_34%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BNo%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20far%20too%20old%20to%20go%20with%20the%20king%20to%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_35%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20am%20eighty%20years%20old%20today%2C%20and%20I%20can%20no%20longer%20enjoy%20anything.%20Food%20and%20wine%20are%20no%20longer%20tasty%2C%20and%20I%20cannot%20hear%20the%20singers%20as%20they%20sing.%20I%20would%20only%20be%20a%20burden%20to%20my%20lord%20the%20king.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_19_36%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2236%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E36%3C%2Fspan%3EJust%20to%20go%20across%20the%20Jordan%20River%20with%20the%20king%20is%20all%2